NAME
    ln - create links

SYNOPSIS
    ln -s <target> <link>
    ln -sf <target> <link>

DESCRIPTION
    Creates symbolic links. The link points to target, which can be
    a relative or absolute path. Hard links are not supported.

OPTIONS
    -s, --symbolic
            Create a symbolic link (required)

    -f, --force
            Remove existing destination file before creating link

EXAMPLES
    ln -s /api/data/users ~/users
        Create symlink to users data in home directory

    ln -s ../shared/config.json /tmp/config
        Create symlink with relative target

    ln -sf /new/target /tmp/link
        Overwrite existing symlink

NOTES
    The target path is stored as-is. Relative targets are resolved
    from the link's directory, not the current directory.

    To view symlink targets, use: ls -l

SEE ALSO
    ls, cp, mv, rm
